stake we used to have good holidays and we enjoyed them. But to go away to stay, I didn't go on a holiday with anyone, I went with me dad in 19 - beginning of 1918 we went to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3039684\charrsid12214547 Morecambe}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5005651\charrsid12214547 , just me dad and myself for a week's holiday. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3039684\charrsid12214547 That\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5005651\charrsid12214547 
 the only time that we've ever been away - for a week's holiday. Just me dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11799755 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5005651\charrsid12214547 These holidays when you went to visit both your parents' families, would they be for a week as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5601259 CT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5005651\charrsid12214547 Yes, they was - they was for the week you see, the - not necessarily the - the feast 
week, it was when me dad has his allocated week, and there was no such things as - going because it was Parish Feast Week or ought of that and we - he - he just have had to wait it because you see we had to have so many attendances at school before we wer
e allowed if we - to go to work. You see, when you went to work you used to - they wanted you to start work - which was at half time - you - that you'd to have so many attendances at school each year. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11799755 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5005651\charrsid12214547 How often would you go on these holidays to stay with relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5601259 CT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5005651\charrsid12214547 Well - it would probably boil down to about once a - once a year and that would be - you know, in the middle - summer period.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11799755 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5005651\charrsid12214547 Which members of the family went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5601259 CT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5005651\charrsid12214547 Oh - all - all the tribe went, in the - in the beginning 'til - the - as they got a bit older, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3039684\charrsid12214547 girls}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5005651\charrsid12214547 
 got a bit older and then - we started to more - but we used to go to the same people. To visit relatives, even so, although - later on we went on our own. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11799755 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5005651\charrsid12214547 Afterwards I suppose the girls would go when the mill was on holiday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5601259 CT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5005651\charrsid12214547 
When the - when the mill was on, yes, they used to go - and - oh I - I've visited the - the same people - I've - I've visited 'em up 'til - 1946, was the last time I went to Brinklow so you can tell it's been a lifetime - visiting them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11799755 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5005651\charrsid12214547 And to Suffolk?
